 GMulti can share a config with NLFind.
@endnode
@remark &&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
@node USAGE "Using GMulti"
 
 Make sure you have @{"installed and set up" link INSTALL} GMulti properly. When this
 has been done GMulti will be run every time you swith your computer on.
 
 GMulti installs itself as a commodity when run, so it can be quit or 
 disabled using exchange.
 
 GMulti supports an additional option (only available if you have added it
 to your user-startup). This option specifies a config file to use rather
 than MAIL:Multiline.cfg eg you might have the following in you user-startup:

@{fg highlight}Run >NIL: <NIL: GMulti Comms:GMulti.cfg@{fg text}
@endnode
